# Coding Workflow Preferences

- Focus on the area of the codebase relevant to the task.
- Do not change unrelated code.
- Check whether a similar solution already exists before creating a new one.
- Preserve established repo patterns unless explicitly asked to change them.
- Think through downstream impact before changing shared types, interfaces, schemas, or contracts.
- Write or update tests for meaningful behavioural changes.
- Prefer completing the correct small change over doing a broad speculative refactor.
- Keep diffs intentional, readable, and easy to review.
